                        <interp inst="t18351123-name-628" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM BANGS</persName>
                  </hi>. I live at No. 40, Clifton-street, Finsbury, and am clerk to Sir John Griffiths. I had a piece of cloth, which was to make me a coat, in a box in my bed-room—the prisoner is my son—my wife told me something, which led me to examine the box—It was open, and ap<lb></lb>peared to have been broken open, and the cloth was gone—I spoke to my son about it—he said he knew nothing of it—this is it.</p>
